'''''Human Capital''''' ({{lang-it|'''Il capitale umano'''}}) is a 2013 Italian film directed by [[Paolo Virzì]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Jay Weissberg|title=Tribeca Film Review: ‘Human Capital’|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/reviews/tribeca-film-review-human-capital-1201157301/|accessdate=25 April 2014|newspaper=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 14, 2014}}</ref> The film is based on the American novel ''Human Capital'' by [[Stephen Amidon]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Charles|first=Ron|title=Film version of Stephen Amidon’s ‘Human Capital’ a hit in Italy|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/style-blog/wp/2014/04/09/update-film-version-of-stephen-amidons-human-capital-a-hit-in-italy/|accessdate=5 May 2014|newspaper=Washington Post|date=9 April 2014}}</ref>  For her performance in the film, [[Valeria Bruni Tedeschi]] was awarded Best Actress at the 2014 [[Tribeca Film Festival]].<ref name="Gordon Cox">{{cite news|last=Gordon Cox|title=Tribeca Film Festival: Israeli Film ‘Zero Motivation’ Scores Two Awards|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/tribeca-film-festival-winners-list-1201163179/|accessdate=25 April 2014|newspaper=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 24, 2014}}</ref> It was selected as the Italian entry for the [[Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Best Foreign Language Film]] at the [[87th Academy Awards]], but was not nominated.<ref name="Italy">{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/oscars-italy-selects-human-capital-735371 |title=Oscars: Italy Selects 'Human Capital' for Foreign-Language Category |accessdate=24 September 2014 |work=Hollywood Reporter}}</ref>

==Plot summary==
The film is set in a town in [[Brianza]] and in [[Milan]]. On Christmas Eve, a waiter cycling home from working at a prestigious private school's gala is hit by a car. The driver flees, leaving the waiter lying in the street badly injured. The waiter is hospitalized and close to death. The next day, two well-known families' lives are connected by the incident.

==Filming locations==
Even though the story is set in a town in Brianza, most of the urban scenes were filmed in February 2013 in the cities of [[Varese]]<ref>{{cite news |title= Virzì svela il "Capitale Umano" E Varese è subito protagonista |url=http://www.laprovinciadivarese.it/stories/Cronaca/virzi-svela-il-capitale-umano-e-varese-e-subito-protagonista_1037918_11/|newspaper=La Provincia di Varese|date=18 December 2013 |location=Varese |access-date=17 June 2015 }}</ref> and [[Como]], in the countryside of [[Osnago]] in the [[Province of Lecco]] and in [[Arese]] for the Villa with the swimming pool.<ref>{{cite news |title="Il capitale umano", Virzì mette a nudo l'élite: "Ecco gli italiani schiavi del denaro"|url=http://www.repubblica.it/spettacoli/cinema/2014/01/06/news/virz-75235095/|newspaper=Repubblica|location=Milan |access-date=17 June 2015 }}</ref> The beautiful Villa of the Bernaschi Family is located in [[Fortunago]], a medieval village in the [[Province of Pavia]].<ref>http://laprovinciapavese.gelocal.it/pavia/cronaca/2013/03/05/news/a-fortunago-le-riprese-del-nuovo-film-di-virzi-1.6638672</ref>

